<dl id="n12063c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12063c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12063c"> 63(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ alliance / serpentcult &amp; Penates</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mais nous avons entendu comment l&apos;a qualifi&eacute; sa m&egrave;re. Elle l&apos;a appel&eacute; &ldquo;une merveille, un miracle, un prodige,&rdquo; en breton <i>Marz</i>. Ce nom magique, qui n&apos;a plus aujourd&apos;hui qu&apos;un sens vulgaire et g&eacute;n&eacute;ral,&hellip; et l&apos;&ecirc;tre qui le porte est le produit incontestable de l&apos;alliance &hellip; entre le culte des enchanteurs de serpents et des esprits familiers <br> <font color="green">[But we know what his mother called him. She called him &ldquo;a marvel, a miracle, a prodigy,&rdquo; in Breton <i><mark>Marz</mark></i>. This magical name, which nowadays only has an everyday, general meaning, brings us also to the Marsi of antiquity, and the being who bears such a name it is the indisputable product of <mark>an alliance, mentioned above, between the snake-charmers&apos; cult and the religion of familiar spirits</mark>]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
